leave any choice to the opponent}) 7... gxf6 (7... Qxf6 $2 8. Ndb5 $18 {
[%cal Gc3d5]}) 8. Nf5 Bxf5 9. exf5 {[%csl Rd5]} d5 (9... Nd4 10. Bc4 {[%csl
Rd5][%cal Gd1h5]} Rc8 11. Bb3 Qd7 12. O-O Qxf5 13. Nd5 Rg8 14. f4 $16 {[%csl
Re8]}) 10. Qxd5 Bb4 11. Bc4 (11. O-O-O $16) 11... Bxc3+ 12. bxc3 Qxd5 13. Bxd5
Rc8 14. O-O-O $16) (6... Qb6 $6 7. Be3 {[%cal Gd4c6]} (7. Nb3 $5) 7... a6 ({
the greedy} 7... Qxb2 $2 {will cost dearly after} 8. Ndb5 Qb4 (8... Nb4 $2 9.
Kd2 $18 {[%cal Ga1b1]}) 9. Bd2 Qc5 10. Rb1 $1 Ng4 11. Qe2 $18 {[%cal Gh2h3,
Gb5c7]}) (7... Bd7 8. Nxc6 Qxc6 9. f3 {[%csl Rc6][%cal Gd1d2,Ge1c1] and White
is apparently faster in the upcoming mutual race, for example} g6 10. Qd2 Bg7
11. O-O-O a6 12. g4 $16) 8. Nb3 Qc7 ({perhaps Black should better reconcile
himself with} 8... Qd8 9. Be2 {[%cal Gg2g4]}) 9. Nd5 $1 Nxd5 10. exd5 Ne5 11.
Be2 e6 12. O-O Be7 13. c4 {[%cal Ga1c1]} O-O 14. Rc1 $16) (6... Qa5 $6 7. Bb5
$1 Bd7 8. Bxf6 (8. Nb3 $5) 8... gxf6 9. Nb3 Qd8 10. Qh5 {[%csl Gh5][%cal Ge1c1]
} Rg8 11. g3 $16) (6... a6 {can be challenged by the surprising} 7. Nxc6 $5 (7.
Qd2 e6 {will lead to well-trodden theory, but}) (7. Qd3 $5 {deserves practical
tests}) 7... bxc6 8. Bc4 {and now:} Qa5 ({after} 8... e6 9. Qe2 {[%cal Ge1c1]
Black must constantly reckon with the central e4-e5 break, e.g.} Be7 10. O-O-O
Qc7 11. Rhe1 (11. h4 $5) 11... O-O 12. e5 dxe5 13. Qxe5 Qxe5 14. Rxe5 $14) (
8... Rb8 9. Bb3) 9. Bd2 ({the most natural reply is} 9. Qd2 h6 10. Bxf6 gxf6
11. O-O-O e6 12. Kb1 $14 {Ganguly - Karthikeyan, chess24.com INT, 2022, but
White has an interesting idea up his sleeve}) 9... Qc7 10. Qe2 g6 11. e5 $5 (
11. O-O-O Bg7) 11... dxe5 12. O-O-O Bg7 13. Rhe1 Nd7 (13... Bb7 14. f4 $1) 14.
Na4 O-O 15. Bc3 $16) 7. Bxf6 exf6 8. Bb5 $1 Bd7 9. Qd2 Bg7 10. O-O-O O-O 11.
Nb3 Be6 (11... Qb6 12. Qxd6 Be6 {transposes to the main text}) ({Black's
intention to open the big diagonal in front of his main asset Bg7 by} 11... f5
$6 {is understandable, but most of the pieces are disappearing after} 12. Qxd6
Be6 13. Qxd8 Rfxd8 14. Bxc6 bxc6 15. exf5 Bxf5 16. Rxd8+ Rxd8 17. Rd1 Bh6+ 18.
Kb1 Rxd1+ 19. Nxd1 $16) (11... a6 $6 12. Bxc6 Bxc6 13. f3 $1 ({a precise
