Qg5+ 11. Kb1 Bg7 12. Nd5 f5 $13) 8... Ne5 (8... Qa5 9. h4 Nxd4 ({in order to
prevent} 9... e6 10. Nb3 Qc7 11. Qg3 $14 {Black reverts to the usual 7.Qd2})
10. Qxd4 h6 11. Bd2 e5 12. Qd3 Qb6 13. f3 $14) (8... e6 9. O-O-O a6 {is the
major alternative, which can be questioned by the fresh approach} 10. Nxc6 $5 (
10. f4) (10. h4) 10... Bxc6 11. Bf4 (11. f4 Be7 $13) 11... d5 (11... e5 $6 {
is an obvious concession -} 12. Bg5) (11... Qb6 $5 12. Rhf1 Be7 (12... Rd8 13.
