O-O O-O 9. Ng3 Be6 {The assessment of this move, which is keeping an eye on
the key d5-square, depends greatly on the more or less forced sequence} 10. Nd5
Nxd5 11. exd5 Bxd5 $5 12. Bxh7+ Kxh7 13. Qxd5 Nc6 14. Nf5 (14. f4 f5 $13) 14...
Qd7 (14... g6 $6 15. Nxe7 (15. Qd3 $5) 15... Qxe7 16. Be3 Rad8 17. Rad1 $14 {
reaches a better version for White of the game, which is featured in the next
