Nc5 {is a signal for} 15. f4 $1 (15. Bc2 b5 $132) 15... exf4 {seems to be
Black's best bet, being based on} (15... Nfd7 16. f5 $36) (15... e4 16. Bc2 b5
{is achieving the desired advance, but White can rely on the same break} 17. f5
bxc4 $140 18. Bb2 $1 Nfd7 19. Qd4 Bf6 20. fxg6 $1 Bxd4 (20... fxg6 21. Rxf6
Qxf6 22. Qxf6 Nxf6 23. Bxf6 cxb3 24. axb3 $16) 21. gxf7+ Kf8 22. fxe8=Q+ Kxe8
23. Bxd4 {with a huge play for the sacrificed queen}) (15... Nxd3 16. Qxd3 exf4
(16... e4 17. Qe2) 17. Bxf4 Nd7 18. Rae1 {is dropping a tempo (Ra8-c8)
compared to the line with 14...Rc8, see below. It is therefore no wonder that
Black is experiencing difficulties, for example} f5 (18... Nc5 $6 19. Qf3 f5
20. b4 Nd7 $140 21. c5 dxc5 22. d6) 19. Nxf5 $1 gxf5 20. Qxf5 $36 Kh8 21. Qf7
