makes sense to revert to} 15. f3 $1 Bg7 (15... h5 16. Ne4 Nh7 17. a4 f5 18. Nf2
Bg7 19. Ra2 {(one more good application of the rook along the vacant second
rank as a consequence of the novelty 14.b3)} Nc5 20. Bb1 a5 $140 $6 21. g4 $1)
16. Rb1 b5 17. Ne4 Nxe4 18. fxe4 b4 19. Be3 Nc5 20. Bc2 {with combined play on
both wings}) (14... Rc8 15. Rb1 Nc5 {is naturally answered with} 16. f4 $1 exf4
