Qxd5 22. Bb3 Qxd1 23. Rfxd1 Rxc1 24. Rxc1 d5 25. Bd2 {with plenty of
compensation for the sacrificed pawn, given the protected passed a5-pawn, the
possession of the c-file and the vulnerability of the b5-pawn.}) 15. f4 exf4 ({
In case of} 15... h4 16. Ne2 ({in case of} 16. Nf5 {Black is by no means
obliged to accept the piece. Instead, he can offer material himself by} Bf8 $5
17. Nxh4 $140 e4 18. Bc2 e3) 16... exf4 {(there is no longer time for Nf6-h5)}
17. Nxf4 {and White can make use of 14.b3 in an original manner after} Ne5 18.
Rb1 Bf8 19. Nh3 Nh7 20. Rb2 Bg7 $140 21. Rbf2 $36) 16. Bxf4 h4 {A logical
follow-up, but the advances in front of the own king have an obvious drawback,
and the imminent knight sacrifice becomes a real one.} (16... Bf8 17. Bg5 $40)
({As said in the notes to 14...Nc5, the insertion of} 16... Nc5 $6 17. Bc2 {
